The Product Flow Step-by-Step:
Onboarding & Personalization: The user signs up and answers a quick, visual 5-question wizard to build their profile (Skin type: Oily/Dry/Sensitive/Combination; Hair type; Concerns: Acne, Aging, Redness; Allergies). This becomes their digital skin passport.
The Dashboard: Clean, premium, and distraction-free. The sidebar displays their recent searches and favorited products. The center provides three simple input channels: Search Bar, URL paste box, or raw Ingredient list paste area.
The Intelligence Engine:
The user inputs "Cetaphil Moisturizing Cream". We clean the query using fuzzy matching.
We extract its ingredient list (either from our local PostgreSQL database, an external skincare API, or directly from the user's manual input).
The engine cross-references each ingredient against our Ingredient Intelligence Database (containing comedogenic ratings, irritants, benefits, and scientific confidence levels).
The Suitability Calculation: We calculate a weighted safety and suitability score. An oily-skinned user gets warned about heavy comedogenic oils (e.g., coconut oil); a sensitive-skinned user sees a warning for synthetic fragrances.
The Verdict & Alternatives: We don't just show numbers; we explain why in plain English. Finally, if the product isn't suitable, we recommend 3 alternative products in the same category that are perfectly aligned with their skin profile and have higher safety scores.
